  m_PrefabAsset: {fileID: 0}
  m_GameObject: {fileID: 353298194}
  m_Enabled: 1
  m_EditorHideFlags: 0
  m_Script: {fileID: 11500000, guid: 045ed7e6f050b7903a9c00ce6c6ac523, type: 3}
  m_Name: 
  m_EditorClassIdentifier: 
  title: Broccoli Terrain Scene
  description: 'This scene contains a Terrain with Broccoli Trees painted on it.


    In
    order to animate BTC tree instances painted on a Terrain it is required to have
    the component  ''Broccoli Terrain Controller'' attached to it. The initial Wind
    parameters are taken from an active directional WindZone GameObject and updated
    by the method BroccoTerrainController::UpdateWind.


    This scene example uses
    a very basic first person controller, so you can move through the terrain to
    better check the trees (use WASD to move and the mouse to look). The wind force
    and direction randomly changes every time a mouse down event is detected.


    Happy
    Tree Designing!'
  autoselectOnSceneLoad: 1
  develShowFields: 1
  scenePipelineType: 0
  detectedPipelineType: 0
  lastSaved: 0
